The subject provides an opportunity to deepen the theoretical knowledge and practical skills in performing various nursing procedures. Nursing procedures focus on adherence to aseptics and antiseptics, waste management principles, compliance with sterility and patient-centered principles.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the subject is to deepen the student's knowledge and skills in performing various nursing procedures in a clinical environment based on the principles of patient-centredness.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student who completed the subject: - is able to follow the requirements of aseptic. antiseptic and the principles of waste management when performing nursing procedures; - is aware and able to follow principles of performing nursing procedures discussed in practicums and is able to perform them independently in a simulated environment; - understands and applies a patient-centered approach to nursing; - is able to administer s/c, i/m, i/v drugs.
